    <div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
        <h4 class="header">Regional Status</h4>
        

        <ul class="text">
        
            <li><b>Mono</b> (341Dd). Stands in the Sweetwater Mountains of Mono Co. (Major and Taylor 1977, Hunter and Johnson 1983) characterize the alliance in California.</li>
        
            <li><b>Sierra Nevada</b> (M261Eo). Stands of <i>Phlox pulvinata</i> appear in an association with <i>Phlox covillei, Elymus elymoides,</i> and <i>Podistera nevadensis</i> above 3500 m in Yosemite National Park.</li>
        
        </ul>
    </div>


    
	
<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Management Considerations</h4>
	<div class="text"> Expansion and contraction of stands in relation to elevation and more mesic alpine stands may be indicators of long-term climatic change. </div>
</div>

    

    

